1. *Napišem* pismo svakog meseca. (I write a letter every month.)
2. Želeo bih da *napišem* roman o svom detinjstvu. (I would like to write a novel about my childhood.)
3. Ona me je molila da joj *napišem* ljubavno pismo. (She begged me to write her a love letter.)
4. Kada sam bio u školi, uvek sam morao da *napišem* sastav. (When I was in school, I always had to write an essay.)
5. Molim te, *napiši* mi kratko pismo da potvrdiš da si primio ovu poruku. (Please write me a brief letter to confirm that you have received this message.)
6. Ovaj put ću *napisati* poruku na lepšem papiru. (This time I will write the message on nicer paper.)
7. Kada *napišem* pismo, obično ga stavim u kovertu. (When I write a letter, I usually put it in an envelope.)
8. Veoma mi je drago da si uspeo *da napišeš* taj izveštaj. (I am very glad that you managed to write that report.)
9. Nadam se da ćeš uspeti *da napišeš* dobru knjigu. (I hope you will be able to write a good book.)
10. Kada *budeš napisao* pismo, pošalji mi ga na mejl. (When you write the letter, send it to me by email.)

Note: In Serbian, the verb "napišem" means "to write" in English. The verb changes its form depending on the tense, aspect, mood, and person.